    <h1 >Learning about div Tag</h1>
    <p >The HTML elements are created using tags. They are grouped by function to help you find what you have in mind easily.</p>
</div>
    <div class="container">
        
        <p>The HTML Content Division element (< div>) is the generic container for flow content. It has no effect on the content or layout until styled using CSS.</p>
        <p>As a "pure" container, the < div> element does not inherently represent anything. Instead, it's used to group content so it can be easily styled using the class or id attributes,<br> marking a section of a document as being written in a different language (using the lang attribute), and so on.</p>
        <p><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/div" target="_blank">To know more about CSS div tag, click here</a></p>
